webpackJsonp([0xf1d0a1383f02],{8789:function(e,t){e.exports={pathContext:{group:[{node:{fields:{title:"Be careful what you wish for",date:"22 Jul 2003",slug:"/2003-07-22-be-careful-what-you-wish-for/",tags:"Y2003"},html:"<p>One thng I've found while blogging is that it's impossible to know in advance what posts will get links. Some posts that I think are important and interesting don't get noticed at all, while some throwaway remark will generate lots of comments and links. </p>\n<p>Or even start a new meme, like my <a href=\"/2003/07/qlinks.php#002426\">joke link</a> to <a href=\"http://entenhausen.blogplan.de\">entenhausen.blogplan.de</a> last week. After seeing the third or fourth city with a <a href=\"blogplan.de\">blogplan</a>, I thought to myself 'next thing you know they'll put one up for Entenhausen' (the home of Donald Duck in German), and I put up a Quick Link. That same morning, the makers of blogplan <i>did</i> put up a map of Entenhausen, giving me <a href=\"http://wiesel.h-blog.org/archives/000169.html\">credit</a> for the 'idea' (do I get royalties as well?), and it now has <s>nearly</s> over 60 blogs entered (PapaScott is on the dolphin).</p>"},next:{fields:{title:"Announcing Blosxom 2.0",date:"22 Jul 2003",slug:"/2003-07-22-announcing-blosxom-20/"}},previous:{fields:{title:"European Baseball: Continental Divide Despite Some Promising Signs",date:"22 Jul 2003",slug:"/2003-07-22-european-baseball-continental-divide-despite-some-promising-signs/"}}},{node:{fields:{title:"Announcing Blosxom 2.0",date:"22 Jul 2003",slug:"/2003-07-22-announcing-blosxom-20/",tags:"Y2003"},html:'<p><a title="Trust Alwin\'s advice, he\'s tried them all!" href="http://ahawkins.org/comments.php?id=P1384_0_1_0">Announcing Blosxom 2.0</a></p>'},next:{fields:{title:"Adventures in disaster recovery",date:"22 Jul 2003",slug:"/2003-07-22-adventures-in-disaster-recovery/"}},previous:{fields:{title:"Be careful what you wish for",date:"22 Jul 2003",slug:"/2003-07-22-be-careful-what-you-wish-for/"}}},{node:{fields:{title:"Adventures in disaster recovery",date:"22 Jul 2003",slug:"/2003-07-22-adventures-in-disaster-recovery/",tags:"Y2003"},html:"<p>Today I found out what happens on a virtual server when the disk space is full and a piece of spam mail arrives.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>The spam gets filtered to the spam folder</li>\n<li>The mail cannot be saved, so return to sender</li>\n<li>The sender is the spam filter, namely me. Send an error message via mail</li>\n<li>The mail cannot be saved, so return to sender</li>\n<li>Repeat <i>ad infinitum</i></li>\n</ol>\n<p>At which point I opted to resize my diskspace. 45 minutes later, we were back online.</p>"},next:{fields:{title:"Would you trust an airline with this map?",date:"21 Jul 2003",slug:"/2003-07-21-would-you-trust-an-airline-with-this-map/"}},previous:{fields:{title:"Announcing Blosxom 2.0",date:"22 Jul 2003",slug:"/2003-07-22-announcing-blosxom-20/"}}}],pathPrefix:"",first:!1,last:!1,index:674,pageCount:1101}}}});
